- **[Work Item Enhancements (Task, Objective, Key Result)](https://gitlab.com/groups/gitlab-org/-/epics/6033)** -- [Prevent double counting data on timebox reports](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/381879) so that iterations and milestones can be defaulted to on for Tasks. Improve the usability of the work item detail view by introducing a [two-column layout](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/415077) and [standardize the workflow for creating planning objects](https://gitlab.com/groups/gitlab-org/-/epics/11012).
- **[Work items are natively supported within Groups](https://gitlab.com/groups/gitlab-org/-/epics/8308)** -- Eliminate the need to maintain projects under groups solely for agile planning purposes, allow teams to consolidate their planning activities at the group level, and enable issues and epics to be migrated to work items. We're currently working on [creating and displaying epic work items in Groups](https://gitlab.com/groups/gitlab-org/-/epics/8778).
- **[Summarize Issue and Epic discussions Beta](https://gitlab.com/groups/gitlab-org/-/epics/10760)** -- View an AI generated summary of all threads and comments within an issue or epic to quickly get up to spead on the discussion. 
- **[Generate Issue Descriptions Beta](https://gitlab.com/groups/gitlab-org/-/epics/10763)** -- When creating new issues or updating existing issue descriptions, use AI to generate a description from a short prompt describing the purpose of the issue. 
